### CREATING A LINUX WORKSPACE AND INSTALLING JUPYTER NOTEBOOK
1. Download Ubuntu from Microsoft Store
2. Run Windows Powershell as Admin, run the following command 
Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux
3. Run Ubuntu, complete the installation and restart the PC as requested
4. Run the following command to download Annaconda3
wget https://repo.continuum.io/archive/Anaconda3-2019.07-Linux-x86_64.sh
Run the following command to unzip and install the package
bash Anaconda3-2019.07-Linux-x86_64.sh
Run the following command to reset the default path
source ~/.bashrc
Run the following command to install jupyter notebook
conda install jupyter notebook
5. To run jupyter notebook, run the command
jupyter notebook
and paste the link provided in your browser to open the root path and you can start coding
### INSTALLING SPORF
6. Run the following commmand
conda install pip
to install pip
7. Run the following command
sudo apt-get update
to update the Ubuntu system
8. Run the following command
sudo apt-get install cmake
to install cmake
9. Run the following command
conda install faiss-cpu -c pytorch
to install libomp.so which is required for SPORF
10. Run the following command
sudo apt-get install libeigen3-dev
to install eigen3 which is also needed
11. Run the following command
sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake python3-dev libomp-dev libeigen3-dev
to prepare build tools
12. Run the following command
pip install --no-binary rerf rerf
to install SPORF
